author: @chokofudgemel1119
text:
MAMA's camerawork did not give justice to their performance but I'm still glad the girls managed to pull it off. Moreover, It's become a rarity these days for kpop artists to perform live along with an extravagant stage and dramatic use of theatrics/ backup dancers.

But man, is IVE (and a few artists) are bringing back that lost art, their performances reminds me a lot of BTS's over the top stages back then and we LOVE to see it. These are prestigious events held at every end of the year for crying out loud, of course everyone should go all out. The only thing missing now is the enthusiastic crowd. (Why are these audiences so dead silent, someone should show them an international crowd during concerts so they know the "PROPER" crowd etiquette when ur faves are performing.)
